rust-proxmox-frr (0.5.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * add local-as setting for BGP neighbors, allowing them to use a different
    AS than the router's primary one when peering.

  * add support for extcommunity lists, mirroring the existing community
    list types.

  * ospf: add `redistribute` setting to import routes from other protocols
    (connected, kernel, static, ...) into OSPF.

  * sdn: ospf: move the NetworkType enum (Broadcast, NonBroadcast,
    PointToPoint, PointToMultipoint) to proxmox-sdn-types so it can be
    shared with proxmox-ve-config without the latter pulling in the
    optional `frr` feature. This is a breaking change for direct users of
    the type.

 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Fri, 15 May 2026 03:43:57 +0200

rust-proxmox-frr (0.4.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * add constructor to prefix list name.

  * change order type to u16. The order in a route map entry is an u16, not an
    u32 - adapt this here to match the actual type inside FRR.

  * implement routemap match/set statements via adjacent tagging, avoiding a
    mix of adjacent / internal tagging and a nesting of types to represent
    match and set statements. This way a single enum can be used to represent
    match / set statements and all variants can be rendered the same by simply
    printing the keys / values.

  * implement support for call and exit action. They're required internally
    for implementing route maps for EVPN zones with an exit node configured,
    but users can also utilize them to create complex route maps via the
    pve-network API / section-config format.

 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 00:30:12 +0200

rust-proxmox-frr (0.3.0-1) trixie; urgency=medium

  * switch FRR config serialization from line-by-line Rust code to jinja
    template rendering, with templates included on compile time from the new
    proxmox-frr-templates package.

  * add BGP configuration types including routers, neighbor groups, address
    families, VRFs, and EVPN support.

  * add IS-IS configuration types and templates.

  * add support for custom FRR configuration lines, prefix lists, ip
    routes, and protocol route-maps.

  * make FrrConfig serde-serializable for Perl interop.

 -- Proxmox Support Team <support@proxmox.com>  Sat, 28 Mar 2026 17:29:24 +0100

